name: MaterialIcons

aliases.name: Style
aliases.type: { shade : Maybe.Maybe MaterialIcons.Shade , inactive : Bool , size : Maybe.Maybe MaterialIcons.Size , flipH : Bool , flipV : Bool , rotation : Maybe.Maybe MaterialIcons.Rotation }

values.name: i
values.comment:
import MaterialIcons as MDI exposing (..)

    myIconStyle : Style
    myIconStyle
      = { shade    = Nothing
        , inactive = False
        , size     = Nothing
        , flipH    = False
        , flipV    = False
        , rotation = Nothing
        }

    myTacoIcon : Html msg
    myTacoIcon
      = MDI.i [ MDI.style myIconStyle ] Taco

values.name: style
values.comment:
stylishFish : Html msg
    stylishFish
      = i [ style 
            { shade    = Just Dark
            , inactive = False
            , size     = Just X36
            , flipH    = True
            , flipV    = False
            , rotation = Just Rotate135
            }
          ]
        Fish

values.name: stylesheet
values.comment:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.materialdesignicons.com/2.1.19/css/materialdesignicons.min.css"/>
Include Material Design 2.1.19 in your Elm project.

    import MaterialIcons as MDI exposing (stylesheet,Icon(..))

    view : Model -> Html msg
    view model
      = div []
        [ stylesheet
        , MDI.i [ MDI.style myIconStyle ] Tooth
        ]
